ðŸ“˜ PRODUCT REQUIREMENTS DOCUMENT (PRD)
Student Result Processing System (SRPS)

For i-FATOSS University, Benin

1. Product Overview
1.1 Product Name

Student Result Processing System (SRPS)

1.2 Product Description

The Student Result Processing System (SRPS) is a web-based academic management system designed to automate student result computation, GPA/CGPA calculation, and result generation at i-FATOSS University, Benin.

The system replaces manual result computation methods with a secure, scalable, and automated platform.

2. Problem Statement

Manual result processing leads to:

Arithmetic errors in GPA/CGPA

Delayed result publication

Data loss and poor record storage

Inconsistent grading standards

Difficulty retrieving past results

Poor security of academic records

The institution requires a centralized, automated system to ensure accuracy, transparency, and efficiency.

3. Product Goals & Objectives
3.1 Primary Goals

Automate GPA & CGPA calculation

Ensure accurate grade computation

Provide secure academic record storage

Allow easy generation of result sheets

Reduce lecturer and admin workload

3.2 Measurable Success Metrics

100% automated GPA/CGPA computation

< 2 seconds result generation time

Zero manual arithmetic errors

Secure role-based access control

99% data integrity consistency

4. Target Users
4.1 Admin

Register students

Register courses

Assign lecturers

Manage grading system

Manage academic sessions & semesters

4.2 Lecturer

Upload student scores

Edit scores (before approval)

Submit results for approval

4.3 HOD (Optional Role)

Review and approve results

4.4 Student

View semester results

View GPA & CGPA

Download printable result sheet

