Node.js

Express.js

MVC architecture

Middleware for authentication

Database:

MongoDB (Mongoose ODM)

8. Database Design (MongoDB Collections)
8.1 Users Collection
{
  name: String,
  email: String,
  password: String,
  role: ["admin", "lecturer", "student"],
  department: String,
  createdAt: Date
}

8.2 Students Collection
{
  userId: ObjectId,
  matricNumber: String,
  department: String,
  level: Number,
  sessionAdmitted: String,
  status: String
}

8.3 Courses Collection
{
  courseCode: String,
  title: String,
  creditUnit: Number,
  department: String,
  level: Number,
  semester: String,
  lecturerId: ObjectId
}

8.4 Results Collection
{
  studentId: ObjectId,
  courseId: ObjectId,
  session: String,
  semester: String,
  CA: Number,
  exam: Number,
  total: Number,
  grade: String,
  gradePoint: Number
}

8.5 GPA Collection (Optional Optimization)
{
  studentId: ObjectId,
  session: String,
  semester: String,
  GPA: Number,
  CGPA: Number
}

